This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with improving acoustic modeling performance in automatic speech recognition tasks for multiple languages. The use of Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) recurrent neural networks (RNN) as building blocks also suggests a focus on natural language processing. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the paper discusses the use of adversarial training to improve the performance of multilingual models. 

cs.SD (Sound) is another possible sub-category because the paper deals with acoustic modeling in speech recognition tasks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category because the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for multilingual acoustic modeling. 

Finally, cs.SD (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category because the paper deals with improving the performance of automatic speech recognition systems.
